{"lemma":"طَبَقاتٌ","slug":"طَبَقاتٌ","root":"ط.ب.ق","root_slug":"ط-ب-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ب-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26336","n26345","n26346"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"layer; stratum; level"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"caste; class"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"storey; floor; level"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tˤa.ba.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26336","headword_ar":"طبّقهُ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTobiyqN","text_ar":"تَطْبِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q Als~aHaAbu Aljaw~a","text_ar":"طبّق السَّحَابُ الجَوَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds covered the mid-air between the heaven and the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algayomu Als~amaA='a","text_ar":"الغَيْمُ السَّمَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTobaqa","text_ar":"اَطْبَقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~aqahaA","text_ar":"طَبَّقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds covered the sky"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh, TA:) both signify the same. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q AlmaA='u wajoha AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"طبّق المَا=ءُ وَجْهَ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water covered the face of the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"طبّق الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a","text_ar":"عَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general, in its relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations, operation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operations, effect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effects,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K.) And as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a","text_ar":"عَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is trans.: so in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA maTarN Tab~aqa","text_ar":"هٰذَا مَطَرٌ طَبَّقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is rain that has included the general extent of the land within the compass of its fall"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q Algayomu","text_ar":"طبّق الغَيْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) inf. n. as above, (S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds rained upon the whole of the land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made their rain common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1825},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTobiyqN","text_ar":"تَطْبِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to suit, match, tally, conform, correspond,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"with another thing. (KL.) ―         -b5-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q bayona Al$~ayoy^ayoni","text_ar":"طبّق بَيْنَ الشَّيْيَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put the two things together, face to face."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See also 3.) ―         -b6-  Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aTobiyqu","text_ar":"التَّطْبِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the divinely-appointed act of prayer is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The putting the hands"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together, palm to palm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the thighs in the act of bowing oneself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) and in like manner"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the act termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~a$ah~ud","text_ar":"التَّشَهُّد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (El-Harbee, TA.) One says of a person bowing himself in prayer,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q","text_ar":"طبّق"},{"kind":"text","text":", and likewise ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ATbq","text_ar":"اطبق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q kaf~ayohi","text_ar":"طبّق كَفَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q bayona kaf~ayohi vum~a waDaEahumaA bayona faxi*ayohi","text_ar":"طبّق بَيْنَ كَفَّيْهِ ثُمَّ وَضَعَهُمَا بَيْنَ فَخِذَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put his hands"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together, palm to palm, ana then put them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between his thighs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) The doing thus is forbidden; (Mgh, O;) for the hands should be placed upon the knees. (O.) ―         -b7-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"horse's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raising his fore feet together and putting them down together in running:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or, accord. to As,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaping"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel, or of a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then alighting so that the legs fall upon the ground together;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the doing of which is not approved. (TA.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~qt","text_ar":"طبّقت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibilu AlT~ariyqa","text_ar":"الاـِبِلُ الطَّرِيقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels travelled the road without declining from the right direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [The verb is there written without any syll. sings; but is evidently thus.]) ―         -b9-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q","text_ar":"طبّق"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayofu","text_ar":"السَّيْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~q Als~ayofu AlmafoSila","text_ar":"طبّق السَّيْفُ المَفْصِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n. as above, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sword hit the joint"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and severed the limb:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell between two bones."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A poet says, (S,) namely, El-Farezdak, praising El-Hajjáj, and likening him to a sword, (O,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yuSam~imu A^aHoyaAnFA waHiynFA yuTab~iqu"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sm","text_ar":"صم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuTab~iqu AlmafoSila","text_ar":"يُطَبِّقُ المَفْصِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hits aright the argument, proof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) and this is also said of an eloquent man. (AZ, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAlabN","text_ar":"قَالَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~aqa","text_ar":"طَبَّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hit upon the right mode of judicial decision:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the text of the tradition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Mgh","TA","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n26345","headword_ar":"طِبْقَةٌ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiboqN","text_ar":"طِبْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places:       -A2-  and also near the end of the same paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26346","headword_ar":"طَبَقَةٌ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[generally signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any one of two or more things that are placed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"situate, one above another; a stage, story,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"floor; a layer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stratum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaqaAtN","text_ar":"طَبَقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAqN","text_ar":"طِبَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaqN","text_ar":"طَبَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in seven places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaqaAtu AlEayoni","text_ar":"طَبَقَاتُ العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The coats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tunics, of the eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"julayodapN","text_ar":"جُلَيْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)] ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaqaAtu Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"طَبَقَاتُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The degrees, ranks, orders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"classes, of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * TA.) [Thus,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaqaAtu Al$~uEaraA='i","text_ar":"طَبَقَاتُ الشُّعَرَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The orders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"classes, of the poets."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubuhu A_ilaY~a TabaqapN","text_ar":"كُتُبُهُ اـِلَىَّ طَبَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase mentioned by Ibn-'Abbád as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His letters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"epistles, to me are consecutive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b5-  A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabaqap","text_ar":"طَبَقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of land is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aArap","text_ar":"مَشَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wr","text_ar":"شور"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}